        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 5:57PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 556 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Cooper Heights, or 8
miles northwest of Lafayette, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel sized hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to exposed surfaces is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ringgold, Fort Oglethorpe, Rossville, Chickamauga, Lookout Mountain,
Chattanooga Valley, Lakeview, Indian Springs, Graysville, Blue
Spring, Wildwood, Fairview, Boynton, Chattanooga  Valley, Cloudland
Canyon State Park, and Cooper Heights.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM EDT for
northwestern Georgia.</instruction>
